name: Journey to The Unexplored #2  | Alone in The Woods |
description:
Better solo travel rather than have annoying partner, right?. It feels nice to spend time alone in the woods, even we still travel as a group. Like go to bushes to take a pee, midnight poo when everyone asleep, hanging on a hammock that placed between two trees far away from other tent. And listening to the silence of earth.



|About Journey to The Unexplored|

Explore can be anything. It can be places, feelings, someone, thoughts, literally anything. This is a collection of my photographs that i captured during the darkest time and post-darkest time of my life. Exploring places is just metaphor for guide us to a deeper meaning.

Shots on 35mm using Fujica M1 analog camera taken in Indonesia.
